This kind of things go back to my mind, sometimes, mostly when I get depressed.Today the sun is shining, kooking and yes I am a bit late, but happy to see the trip ahead of me literally: minivans were queued, the heavy truck being one of them. It pulled out first, following the following, about 10 min. later, leaving me safe and sound.La Gran Via de Colon a Paitilla Running ahead of the boys..Perfect time, I feel lucky, the terra firma sounds solid under my feet.I can see huge cranes building Panama Bay Terraces towers where Millennium will stand, one of them is already completed.Miraflores is taking shape, leaning away the north end, a viewpoint from where an old termite excavated and rebuilt at its will an old train crossing from urban railroad, to become a new signaling station to mark the direction and future entry of our millennium in the western hemisphere. Watching out of awe of balconies on the Miramar section structure, Panamanians wonder what would the final piece to our jigsaw puzzle should be? Another skyscraper? A Tower?
